00:04:34.000 --> 00:04:38.000
And what this means is that the progenitor of these two genes  

00:04:38.000 --> 00:04:42.000
must've already existed at the time that the flies and we diverged,   

00:04:42.000 --> 00:04:46.000
which six or seven-hundred million years ago, and in the intervening  

00:04:46.000 --> 00:04:50.000
six or seven-hundred million years,  these genes have been totally  

00:04:50.000 --> 00:04:53.000
unchanged.  i.e., once the gene was developed,   

00:04:53.000 --> 00:04:57.000
evolution could not tinker with it,  and begin to change it in different  

00:04:57.000 --> 00:05:00.000
ways, ostensibly because such tinkering would render these genes  

00:05:00.000 --> 00:05:04.000
dysfunctional,  and thereby would inactivate them,   

00:05:04.000 --> 00:05:08.000
thereby depriving the organism of a critical sensory organ.   

00:05:08.000 --> 00:05:11.000
So here we have an example,  a dramatic example, of how  

00:05:11.000 --> 00:05:15.000
morphology misleads us.  Here we have an example of where we  

00:05:15.000 --> 00:05:18.000
would say these two eyes,  the two eyes I've shown you here,   

00:05:18.000 --> 00:05:22.000
are so different from one another that they must,   

00:05:22.000 --> 00:05:26.000
