00:05:33.000 --> 00:05:37.000
a prototypical eye, whose precise morphology we can't discern anymore.   

00:05:37.000 --> 00:05:41.000
And so we begin to realize that if we really want to understand  

00:05:41.000 --> 00:05:44.000
evolution and we really want to understand phylogeny,   

00:05:44.000 --> 00:05:48.000
phylogeny being how the species are related to one another,   

00:05:48.000 --> 00:05:52.000
we have to the DNA, and we have to begin to look not at phenotype,   

00:05:52.000 --> 00:05:56.000
but we have to look instead, at genotype.   

00:05:56.000 --> 00:06:01.000
The Darwinian model is pretty much like this, the survival of the  

00:06:01.000 --> 00:06:06.000
fittest.  And when I say that,  we imagine that we have here, a  

00:06:06.000 --> 00:06:11.000
genetically heterogeneous group of organisms within a species,   

00:06:11.000 --> 00:06:16.000
and this, this number of individuals in the species could be 100,   

00:06:16.000 --> 00:06:22.000
it could be 1,000,000.  This particular individual,   

00:06:22.000 --> 00:06:27.000
by chance, acquires a mutation,  or an advantageous allele, through  

00:06:27.000 --> 00:06:32.000
some genetic alteration.  This genotype renders this organism  

00:06:32.000 --> 00:06:36.000
more fit, phenotypically,  has a selective advantage and  

00:06:36.000 --> 00:06:40.000
consequently, over extended periods of time, which may be thousands or  

00:06:40.000 --> 00:06:44.000
even millions of years,  the descendents of the organism  

00:06:44.000 --> 00:06:48.000
bearing this allele now have advantage, have greater reproductive  

00:06:48.000 --> 00:06:52.000
advantage, survival advantage,  compared with the other individuals  

00:06:52.000 --> 00:06:56.000
in the same species,  and therefore, the representation of  

00:06:56.000 --> 00:07:00.000
this mutant allele in the gene pool of the species becomes expanded.   

00:07:00.000 --> 00:07:03.000
When I say gene pool,  I'm talking bout the common shared  

00:07:03.000 --> 00:07:07.000
set of genes within the species,  such as within the human species.   

00:07:07.000 --> 00:07:10.000
And so eventually, the descendents of this organism,   

00:07:10.000 --> 00:07:14.000
or the descendants of an organism bearing this allele,   

00:07:14.000 --> 00:07:17.000
now become overrepresented in the population, because they're more fit.   

00:07:17.000 --> 00:07:21.000
And then there can be another succession, i.   

00:07:21.000 --> 00:07:24.000
., there could be other mutations occurring subsequently.   

00:07:24.000 --> 00:07:28.000
Once again, favoring the selective outgrowth of an individual bearing  

00:07:28.000 --> 00:07:31.000
this allele, or this allele.  And in addition,   

00:07:31.000 --> 00:07:35.000
there can be the process of what one calls, speciation.   

00:07:35.000 --> 00:07:38.000
That is to say, that if some parts of the species live in one place,   

00:07:38.000 --> 00:07:42.000
and other parts of the species live in another place,   

00:07:42.000 --> 00:07:45.000
geographically, they may no longer interbreed, and as a consequence,   

00:07:45.000 --> 00:07:49.000
and because of the fact they're under different selective pressures,   

00:07:49.000 --> 00:07:52.000
they may begin to diverge from another if, evolutionary speaking,   

00:07:52.000 --> 00:07:56.000
because they're no longer actively exchanging genes within one another.   

00:07:56.000 --> 00:08:00.000
And, as a consequence, one can have new species arriving.   

00:08:00.000 --> 00:08:03.000
And what one believes,  this happens over slow,   

00:08:03.000 --> 00:08:07.000
slowly over evolutionary time,  but it does arise, and to the extent  

00:08:07.000 --> 00:08:11.000
it does, one eventually ends up with organisms here and here,   

00:08:11.000 --> 00:08:15.000
which can no longer effectively interbreed with one another.   

00:08:15.000 --> 00:08:18.000
That is to say, they become genetically so different from one  

00:08:18.000 --> 00:08:22.000
another, that any hybrids formed between them are,   

00:08:22.000 --> 00:08:26.000
in fact, sterile, for one reason or another, if they're at all  

00:08:26.000 --> 00:08:30.000
