00:08:37.000 --> 00:08:40.000
closely or similarly related are their DNA sequences?   

00:08:40.000 --> 00:08:44.000
If, distantly related organisms have very distantly related  

00:08:44.000 --> 00:08:48.000
sequences, and closely related organisms must have sequences which  

00:08:48.000 --> 00:08:51.000
are very similar to one another.  And over evolutionary time, there's  

00:08:51.000 --> 00:08:55.000
a so-called mutational clock,  where one, where each species  

00:08:55.000 --> 00:08:59.000
accumulates a certain number of point mutations,   

00:08:59.000 --> 00:09:02.000
base substitutions in it's DNA,  per million years, and the longer  

00:09:02.000 --> 00:09:06.000
the two species are separated from one another, the greater will be the  

00:09:06.000 --> 00:09:10.000
difference in their sequence diversity.   

00:09:10.000 --> 00:09:14.000
